  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility package for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package is structurally complete and plausible but omits hasApplicabilityConstraint and hasOperatingEnvelope from the ContextOfUse, leaving the model's valid operating range unspecified in structured form (W-ON-02). All 13 credibility factors are addressed; 7 are formally assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 are flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps consistent with MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cou2-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
