      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, round-off error, and solver tolerance sensitivity must all be formally characterized for the hemolysis prediction workflow.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error not formally assessed. Residual convergence criteria are reported but iterative error bounding and round-off analysis are absent. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 reflects no structured assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
