      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal use-error analysis must document analyst-induced variability in mesh generation, boundary condition setup, and post-processing for the hemolysis workflow.",
      "rationale": "Use error not assessed. No inter-analyst variability study or formal checklist for hemolysis CFD setup was conducted. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The power-law hemolysis model and turbulence closure must be formally justified against alternative model forms with sensitivity analysis; model-form uncertainty must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty not assessed. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was adopted without comparison to alternative hemolysis models. Turbulence model sensitivity not evaluated. Flagged as critical epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (fluid viscosity, hemolysis model coefficients, rotational speed) must be characterized with probability distributions and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was nominally performed but input probability distributions for hemolysis model coefficients were not derived from experimental data; uniform distributions with arbitrary bounds were assumed. Input characterization flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
